## windows-and-copilot-logs.md
# Windows / Git Bash gotchas

- Running native `node.exe` under Git Bash (MINGW/winpty) with redirected or
  piped stdin (`node x.mjs < file`, `echo .. | node`) prints "stdin is not a tty"
  to stderr and can exit 1. This is a winpty artifact, NOT a script bug.
  To test stdin-reading scripts cleanly, spawn node-from-node with stdio pipes,
  or run via the real runtime. Copilot hooks pipe stdin cleanly (no winpty).

# Copilot session debug logs
- Location (Windows): %APPDATA%\Code[- Insiders]\User\workspaceStorage\<wsId>\
  GitHub.copilot-chat\debug-logs\<sessionId>\main.jsonl
- Visual Studio is DIFFERENT: no JSONL spans. It writes an unstructured text
  trace at %LOCALAPPDATA%\Temp\VSGitHubCopilotLogs\<stamp>_VSGitHubCopilot.chat.log
  (format: "[ts Category Level] message"). No prompts/tools/commands/reasoning
  are parseable; only metadata (start/end ts from bracketed lines, "Copilot chat
  version X", "VS: ...", "Session: <guid>"). VS does NOT run .github/hooks Stop
  hooks, so session-keeper auto-capture is VS Code-only; VS = manual run, which
  just copies the trace log + writes a metadata summary.
- main.jsonl is line-delimited spans: keys ts,dur,sid,type,name,spanId,status,attrs.
- Terminal commands = spans where name=="run_in_terminal", attrs.args is a JSON
  string {command,explanation,goal,mode}, attrs.result holds output.
- File edits: spans named create_file / replace_string_in_file (attrs.args.filePath).
- Agent's VISIBLE replies (the chat messages, e.g. final summary) = text parts of
  agent_response.attrs.response (JSON-array-string; parts type text vs tool_call).
  session-keeper writes these full to responses/<session>.md (separate from
  thinking/ which is attrs.reasoning). allAssistantText() concatenates all text parts.
- $VSCODE_TARGET_SESSION_LOG points at the active session's debug-log folder.
- MODEL-AGNOSTIC parsing: key off span type/name, NOT model name. Models seen:
  claude-opus/sonnet/haiku, gpt-4o-mini, gemini, vscode-agentic-search-router.
  Reasoning is ALWAYS at agent_response.attrs.reasoning (a string). The SKILL's
  old claim that reasoning is also in llm_request as type:"reasoning" parts is
  FALSE — that string never appears in any log. Models w/o reasoning (gpt-4o-mini,
  router) just have none. response = JSON-array-string of {parts:[{type:text|tool_call,
  content}]}, but SOMETIMES a plain non-JSON string — handle both. Sessions can
  switch models mid-way; aggregate models table by attrs.model (clean id, no chat: prefix).

# Tauri 2.0 beforeDevCommand cwd gotcha
- beforeDevCommand / beforeBuildCommand in tauri.conf.json run from the dir where
  `tauri dev` is invoked (the package.json dir, e.g. desktop/), NOT from the
  src-tauri/ config dir. frontendDist IS relative to the config file (src-tauri/).
  So in Axiomic: frontendDist="../../web/dist" but beforeDevCommand="pnpm --dir ../web dev".
  Mixing them up gives ENOENT on a wrong path like D:\...\web.

